import { forwardRef } from "react";

useRef()
=======
useRef is a hook that allows you to create a reference  to a DOM node or a javascript Object.
It can be used to access a DOM node directly, or to stroe a value that should not cause a re-render when it changes.

Syntax:
-------
//create a useRef instance

const myRef = useRef(initialValue);

//Access and modify the reference

myRef.current = newValue;

. myRef is the object returned by useRef hook.
. myRef.current is the property you can access and modify. this property holds the value you assigned to it.
. You can read or modify myRef.current as needed within your componenet.


forwardRef
----------
A forward ref is a way to pass a ref through a component to a child component.
It allow you to access the ref of a child component from the parent Component.
